# Commit Message Guidelines

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

## Type

- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `docs`: Documentation only
- `style`: Formatting, whitespace
- `refactor`: Code change (not bug fix or feature)
- `perf`: Performance improvement
- `test`: Tests
- `build`: Build system or dependencies
- `ci`: CI configuration
- `chore`: Other changes (not src/test)
- `revert`: Revert previous commit

## Scope (optional)

Package name or area: `storybook-dark-mode`, `deps`, `config`

## Subject

- Imperative present tense: "change" not "changed"
- Lowercase first letter
- No trailing dot
- Concise and descriptive

## Body (optional)

- Additional context
- Explain "why" not "what"
- Separated by blank line

## Footer (optional)

- Reference issues: `Closes #123`, `Fixes #456`
- Breaking changes: `BREAKING CHANGE: description`

## Examples

```
feat: add dark mode toggle component
feat(storybook-dark-mode): add theme persistence to localStorage
fix: correct dark mode class application on iframe
feat!: remove DarkModeStore from public exports

BREAKING CHANGE: DarkModeStore is now internal. Use DarkModeParam type instead.

feat: add support for custom theme classes

Allow users to specify custom class names for dark and light modes.

Closes #123
```

## Best Practices

1. Subject line under 72 characters
2. Body explains what/why, not how
3. Reference issues when applicable
4. Use imperative mood
5. Be consistent with scope

